reviews.review_text: Contrary to the negative views people have of this location, I had a very good experience. Service was fast, food was good and staffs were friendly and helpful. I didnt get the wrong order.... Sometimes we customers need to be a little patient and considerate... I highly recommend....

My food was ok. I only ordered an iced capp. No problems. They were busy for a Monday afternoon. Or maybe the cashier area and the waiting area is too small...The eating area was cleaned and organized - As was the washroom. I will come back later for some food and check how is the food quality.
Busy area here, be prepared to wait 10 plus minutes if their busy.

Whoever is doing the hiring for this location needs to know they re doing an amazing job at hiring cashiers. Every time I ve gone to this location the staff has been THE most enthusiastic, happy and cheerful individuals working at the till facing the public. Aside from that the orders have always been accurate, on time and overall excellent. Probably some of the best experiences at a McDonald s of any from around the Lower Mainland. Koodos to Brentwood McDonald s!

Great location. Im in and out within 5 minutes every time . If you re complaining about wait time its because you re ordering from the till. Learn how to use the touch screens its not hard or order on the app.
Honestly I eat here about two-three times a week getting quick snacks or dinner and I ve barely had an issues except for once or twice.
Busy, need crew to clean up dining and washroom especially during pandemic. Garbage is always full when we went there 3 times already.
A large McDonald outlet right next to Brentwood station. It has ample sitting space inside and outside. Its located at a prime location.
McDonalds new place is cozy, clean and with a top floor dinning spot. Totally I loved it
Te staff s ts such a good tone and vibe , you can tell they love their work environment.
One of the best place to sit around enjoy the day and have some delicious food with best drinks!
The staff members were friendly and co-operative. The location is clean and patio dine area is clean too.
Very nice view from the dinning area. Always come around to get a coffee.
Best Big Mac Ive ever had! Fast service too
They improved a lot recently.
Very nice staff
The best in the area!
Good hamburger
Great Experience
Fast friendly service,clean and easy to get around.I would recommend if you are driving or coming off the train and need a coffee.There is also a large donut selection at this location.

Ordered via the app and it worked like a charm. Only issue is they gave me the wrong chicken nugget sauce. This location doesnt offer a lot of seating so i suggest just taking the food togo and eat it near the fountain where the view is better anyway.

This is a two-level McDonalds. Order on ground-level, eat at top level. The service is normally good. One annoyance is when I ordered a decaf and I had to wait five minutes to brew. The seating area is good and spacious. Not entirely the safest area. You can have some shady patrons here.

I get my coffee here when I visit my friend at the Amazing Brentwood. This is a sick McDonalds location. Its built for self-serve so its a really fast experience, I personally like it. Its also a double decker store, my only issue and worry here is the accessibillity of the washrooms being on the second floor - dont recall seeing a way for anyone with acessibillty needs to get up there.
Busy McDonald s location. The staff do try their best but orders can take a while to be completed due to the volume they get.
As of August 14, 2021 still not open, but seems like theres some activity (hiring and opening soon sign).
Good customer service late night was busy but i got my food on time and it was hot and fresh
Not super quick but good service.
lack of sympathy in the staff

Nice place and also right beside the mall Good place to hang out
always good
hit or miss. fast service.

In general it is good, the facilities are nice and the service is fast but the bathrooms were not in good condition and we witnessed a disturbance with teenagers that was resolved by the staff of the place.
reviews.review_translated_text: En general esta bien, las instalaciones son lindas y el servicio es rapido pero los banos no estaban en buenas condiciones y presenciamos un disturbio con adolescentes que fue resuelto por personal del lugar.

reviews.review_text: Ordered breakfast this morning and I was one of the first to arrive. Ordered my usual but now its not edible because the bagel is stale. Its a hockey puck. If only I could go back and get my money back. Not cool you guys. I brought back my order and talked to the manager and she was very understanding and gave the option for a new one. Thank you to the manager.

First time here and the restaurant had a weird layout of 3 compact floors not any other Mcdonalds in Metro Vancouver. This place is not meant for elderly or people disabilities going up stairs to find seating on the 2nd or 3rd floor.
Service was slow, but our order was correct, no mistakes.

I have genuinely have no idea about the 1 star reviews but Ill take it, for what I know, our experience here was completely normal, this is by far for what I know, one of the McDonalds with the biggest kitchen Ive ever seen. Gives us less space but the upstairs seating gives a bit more space to make up for it, for some reason the waiting area for your order is small, and gives less space for a dine in, overall I wouldnt say its bad and one my favourites, its just a fast food chain there that exists. Also Ive noticed that their not open 24/7, which is stupid by me, overall I think you should go outside to the fountain and eat there, but I think were lucky we got upstairs.

This is the prettiest and most technological McDonalds Ive been to so far. They even have handicapped door buttons you can use your foot! (I want to give a 5 star just for that. Its so cool!) But it was really small, and they close the upper floor at night. But the reason Im giving a 3 star was because the staff gave us spoons for our icecream, and put it ON THE COUNTER. Where cash, coins and peoples hands TOUCH. I worked at multiple food industry places. If he did that in my workplace, he wouldve gotten fired immediately. I hope the other staff have basic food safe knowledge, and training because that alone is a huge red flag. (I ended up asking for 2 more spoons instead of grabbing it from the counter)

reviews.review_text: This McDonald s is just fine. They are great sometimes but when they are not they absolutely suck. I ordered a Quarter Pounder without Cheese and a Orange Juice. I also got a snack wrap for my friend. Their Orange juice was watery and the burger lacked sauce. This was a time that they sucked. Good but I recommend Metrotown or Still Creek over this. This is probably the best if you are close by and need a small thing.
The McDonalds itself is fairly standard, usually busy with the mall, towers, and transit hub here.
Convenient location with good seating. But it is not enough chair

love that this place is finally open. will be my go to for sure. however i ordered a large fries and got a 1/3 of sad stale ones, don t worry i ll still keep coming back but please make sure i get what i need when drunk
Great food, fast service, but full garbage bins and trash on tables/floor 30 minutes before closing
They always get my order right, so cant complain. It does seem its Preffered you order on the self serve or phone app.
